cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about improving the accuracy of MobileNets, a type of convolutional neural network commonly used in computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel architecture unit, which involves designing a new bottleneck structure, so it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
